SIMPLE: ineptitude
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ineptitude
<hw>In*ept"i*tude</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>ineptitudo</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality of being inept; unfitness; inaptitude;
unsuitableness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That <qex>ineptitude</qex> for society, which is frequently the
fault of us scholars.</q> <rj><qau>Tatler.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Absurdity; nonsense; foolishness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ineptly</ent>⟦br⟧
